text:
One little two little three little four little 
Five little elephants

Going through the jungle 
Crossed a long bridge

One got bit by an ant
“One two three four”counted their mother
“Why only four of you?”
The four little elephants scratched their heads and kept on walking through

One little two little three little and four little 
Five little elephants

Going through the jungle 
Swam across a river

One lost his under pants
“One two three” counted their mother
“Why only three of you?”
The three little elephants scratched their heads and kept on walking through

One little two little 
Three little elephants

Going through the jungle 
Climbed a tall mountain

One fell down the slant
“One two” counted their mother
“Why only two of you?”
The two little elephants scratched their heads and kept on walking through

One little Two little elephants
Two little elephants

Going through the jungle 
Crossed a long meadow

One went to sleep in a tent
“One” counted their mother
“Why only two of you?”

The one little elephant scratched its head
And kept on walking through

Five, Four, Three, Two
One little elephant

Going through the jungle 
Across the desert

Slipped into the sand
“I’m right here”, called out their mother
“Come back all of you!”

The five little elephants came right back
And said “Mommy thank you!”
